  "prompt": "How long does it take to grow hair after a person has shaved his/her head? What's the regular growth rate?",
  "response": "After shaving the head, hair typically begins to grow back at an average rate of about half an inch (approximately 1.25 centimeters) per month. This rate can vary slightly depending on several factors, including genetics, age, health, and hair type. Generally, most people can expect to see noticeable hair growth within a few weeks, with a full head of hair usually taking several months to grow back completely, often around six to twelve months for a significant length.",
